what  about api_data_agent?

There isn’t an agent named "api_data_agent" available here. Quick summary of what’s possible and why you saw the limitation:

- entity_management_agent: can create, update, search, delete entities in your Cyoda environment (this is the agent you should use for entity ops).
- Limitation: the environment-bound agents (including entity_management_agent) cannot make arbitrary external HTTP requests to public APIs (so they can’t directly call https://cataas.com from here).
- That’s why I asked you to either (A) provide the CATAAS JSON results or (B) run a script locally (which can call CATAAS) that then posts entities to Cyoda.

What I can do for you now (pick one):
1) Option A — You paste/upload the JSON returned by:

2) Option B — I generate a ready-to-run ingestion script (Python or Node). You run it (it will fetch CATAAS and call the Cyoda Data API with your client_id/client_secret/cyoda_host). I can provide the script and instructions, and then you can share results/logs if you want me to verify or re-ingest.

3) Option C — If you prefer repo/deployment approach, I can add an ingestion processor to the branch and deploy (we discussed this earlier), but you asked to avoid repo/deploy — so I’m keeping this as an option only.

You already gave client_id/client_secret and cyoda_host, so if you choose A I can proceed immediately once you paste the API JSON. If you choose B, tell me Python or Node and I’ll produce the script. Which option do you want?
